A call out to all Spartans and Spartan supporters!

Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, 1600 blood drives across the state have been cancelled. Our state‚Äôs blood supply is critically low. Ash Fork Student Council has chosen to honor their commitment to support Arizona‚Äôs blood supply and continue to host their first blood drive of the 2020-2021 school year.

When: Wednesday, August 26th

Time: 12:30 PM-5:30 PM.

Where: In the school multi-purpose room/cafeteria.

*****All CDC guidelines will be followed. Masks are required, and extras are available as needed.*****

Schedule your appointment to donate at bloodhero.com Sponsor Code: ashforkschool
You can also call 928-637-2561 ex 2 to schedule an appointment. Walk ins are always welcome.

Remember to bring a photo ID, hydrate well, and always stay Spartan strong!!

post_text: Dear Senior Parents/Guardians: I was hoping that your graduate had given you information on graduation. I'm finding out differently! Parking is limited and some people have already brought their vehicles to the gate. It is advised that a truck should be backed in for people to sit in. You may start entering the field at 6:30 PM. Remember that you must have a ticket to enter. Tickets were given to your child yesterday. Sorry, but each graduate is limited to 8 people, no exceptions. Ticket holders will need to bring their own lawn or camping chair to sit on, or even a blanket. We will not be setting up chairs for attendees. We will be attempting a LIVE stream on our Facebook account, @AFspartans31. Graduation will begin at 7 PM.

post_text:
Dear kindergarten students, families, and friends,
There will be a kindergarten drive through promotion ceremony in front of Ash Fork School on Tuesday, May 19th at 12:00 noon. The Ash Fork teachers, administration, and staff will be lined up in front of the school to cheer and greet the kindergarten students as they drive by in front of the school. No students or parents are allowed to leave their vehicles due to the social distancing restrictions. Please do not park your vehicles to approach the staff or the school. Mrs. Williams, the kindergarten teacher, will have a certificate and goody bag to hand to kindergarten students. Mrs. Williams will bring the certificates and bags to the vehicles so that students and family members can remain safely in their vehicles. We look forward to celebrating all of the kindergarten students that have worked so hard this school year. See you on May 19th at 12:00 noon!

post_text:
AzMerit 2019 Perfect Scores
Some great recognition for some of our outstanding students. We had six of our students score 100% on their AzMerit Math test last year. Those students are: Sol Ayala, Victor Ayala, Dexter Alldridge, Kameron Johnson, Bear Staples, and Delores White. Sol Ayala not only scored a 100% on her AzMerit Math test, but alos scored a 100% on her ELA. This is also Victor Ayala's second year in a row he scored a 100% on his math. Each of these students will receive a check for $100 for their outstandiing performance on the AzMerit test. Sol will receive $200. Checks will be mailed out next week. Congratulations to these awesome students!!

post_text:
The staff at Ash Fork Schools and your children have worked too hard to let our academic growth be diminished during the Covid-19 emergency. Administrators, teachers, and staff members are currently working on ways to empower our families to continue learning at home.
Many resources will be computer based but we are also looking into ways to help families that do not have access to computers. This will be a great test of both our academic staff and caring families, but together we can make some amazing things happen!

post_text: Ash Fork Schools will begin providing boxed breakfast and lunch meals for children in the community on March 23rd, 2020 between 9-11 AM. The package will contain both breakfast and lunch in order to save the burden of taking two trips per day. These meals will be very basic and utilized for children in need and depend on the school's food program to sustain adequate nutrition. More information will be given on how the food will be distributed.

post_text:
Due to the outstanding commitment of our students, staff and community to Ash Fork schools annual blood drives, our school has won, the highest percentage of participation in the state wide high school challenge for blood donors. We compete against all other high schools in the state and have kept this top award for the past 6 years in a row!!!!!
Our student donors, STUCO blood drive committee members and selected staff, will be guests at the Diamond Back baseball game on April 15th. We will be honored mid field prior to the first pitch and get to enjoy the game in one of the VIP party suites!

Thank you one and all for supporting our blood drives and keeping us as Number 1.
Way to go SPARTANS!!!!

post_text: High school varsity soccer finishes their season with a win against Basis of Flagstaff.(6-1). Thank you seniors (Alex Keele, Marco Ayala, Chris Vazquez, and Brian Martinez) for a great building year. You helped these boys out a lot and made it fun for them. They learned a lot and hopefully they continue to grow. JV has one last game Friday, in St. Michaels.

post_text: Mr. Wood will be taking any interested students to the Northern Arizona College and Career Fair at Flagstaff High School on Thursday, October 24th. Bus will leave at 4:45pm and will return to school at approximately 9:00pm. Over 100 booths from colleges and employers will be present at this fair. Interested students should sign up with Mr. Wood no later than Monday, October 21st.
